            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot. Garden, ¶ 8/4/68. ¶  ¶ Suddenly an apportunity has arisen, dear and honorable Sir, to send a case with plants direct to Perth. Thus I have despatched to you a number of prominently usef...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">68.04.08a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Frederick Barlee</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Colonial Secretary's Office - letters received, acc. 36, vol. 610, ff. 170-2, State Records Office of Western Australia, Perth.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">Transcribed 28.2.90. To be proof read.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Melbourne bot. Garden,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">8/4/68.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Suddenly an apportunity has arisen, dear and honorable Sir, to send a case with plants direct to Perth. Thus I have despatched to you a number of prominently useful plants, all of which are likely to thrive about Swan-River. If there not already exist pines in some variety, you many find those now sent, eligible for the decoration of the ground of some of your public buildings. The plants should be taken out of the pots and planted at once during the genial autumnal weather and it will be needful to place around them rather densely a lot of branches of any kind, in order that the plants may be protected against winds and sudden changes of the temperature.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful salutation</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
