            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">2 Quercus Suber Cork-oak.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">On [<seg style="font-weight: bold; ">date</seg>] Barlee minuted: 'Will the Collectors of Customs be good [<seg style="font-weight: bold; ">enough</seg>] to have the case […] attended to carefully landed and forwarded to Perth without delay? […] to return the letter.' The <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">[position]</seg>, M. Clifton replied on 4 May: 'No vessel appears to be named. If the case of Plants is on board the "H Nicholson" I will endeavour to get it up to Perth tomorrow &amp; if in any other vesel that may arrive from Melbourne I will not fail to attend to this memo.' Barlee added the same day: 'Let a copy of this list be given to Murray the Gardener with a copy of the directions in Dr Müellers letter marked " " in pencil, and see that he keeps a look out for the case and at once attend to the directions.' 'R.P.' annotated also on the same day: 'Done'.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
